Entry.JapaneseText: <Annie>、何をしているんだ、 図鑑を広げて……
Entry.EnglishText: <Annie>, what are you doing with that encyclopedia?

Entry.JapaneseText: <Tytree>さんが食べ過ぎて気持ち悪いって 言うから、胃薬になる草を探してるんです。
Entry.EnglishText: <Tytree> said that his stomach was upset because he ate too much, so I'm looking for an herb to use as medicine.
How about we leave him behind instead?

Entry.JapaneseText: そんな……冷たいじゃないですか……
おう、どうしたんだ、<Annie>、 図鑑なんか広げて。
Entry.EnglishText: Oh, what are you doing looking through that encyclopedia, <Annie>?

Entry.JapaneseText: え？ だって、<Tytree>さん、 気持ち悪いって……
Entry.EnglishText: Huh? But, <Tytree>, didn't you say you weren't feeling well...?

Entry.JapaneseText: あ、あれか。もうすっかり大丈夫みたいだ。 すまないな、ありがとよ、<Annie>。
Entry.EnglishText: Oh, right. It looks like I'm all better now. Sorry about that. Thanks, <Annie>.

Entry.JapaneseText: わたし、もう心配しません……
Entry.EnglishText: That's the last time I'm going to help you with anything!
